title: Liberty's Samantha Peterson, Madelyn Conrad win District 11 Class AAA tennis doubles title
text:
Liberty's Samantha Peterson, coach Leo Schnalzer and Madelyn Conrad after the two Hurricanes seniors won the District 11 Class AAA doubles gold on Monday. (Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com) By Josh Folck | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 19, 2015 5:12 PM, updated October 19, 2015 5:58 PM View/Post Comments 
Samantha Peterson/Madelyn Conrad (Liberty) def. Kaitlyn Swint/Natalie Sinai (Freedom) 6-0, 6-1 â€” Rapid Recap 
Liberty seniors Samantha Peterson and Madelyn Conrad won the District 11 Class AAA doubles title with a dominant 6-0, 6-1 victory over Freedom 's Natalie Sinai and Kaityn Swint on Monday afternoon at Lehigh University. 
Turning point : The Hurricanes seniors used their experience to control freshman Sinai and junior Swint throughout the match. The Patriots pair was only able to get on the scoreboard in the fourth game of the second set. 
What it means : Peterson and Conrad won the title after losing by a 6-0, 6-1 score to the powerful Poje sisters of East Stroudsburg South in last year's final. The senior duo advances to the state tournament on Nov. 6 in Hershey.
